description:
Devops gospel is widespread, but what happens to big legacy
infrastructures? The switch to Continuous Delivery is hard:

-  customers are reluctant to disruptive changes;
-  old operation teams must adapt to new technologies.

We’ll show how a light Test Driven approach to system delivery allowed
us to:

-  reduce software updates time;
-  eliminate maintenance issues;
-  contribute to open source;

The operation team had no troubles thanks to the fast learning curve of
python.

The library we contribute has been included in Red Hat 389 Directory
Server.
